cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI

This paper deals with natural language processing and semantic modeling of events in text, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of RDF representations and cross-document event coreference also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of semantic anomaly to define differences between relations, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and semantic web (cs.SI) sub-categories.
